US OPEN, 2021

6
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:29,160
In 2021, the US Open debuted its first ever NFT collection.

7
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:35,160
The collectibles ranged from limited edition ticket stubs to “golden ace” tokens.

8
00:00:35,820 --> 00:00:42,990
These offered in-person experiences with tennis champions such as Venus Williams and Andy Roddick,

9
00:00:43,530 --> 00:00:48,180
giving fans another way to engage with, and commemorate the experience.

10
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:54,480
After the sale, the NFT marketplace Bitski saw that this NFT collection

11
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:59,280
brought an entirely new community of people into the world of NFTs

12
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:03,480
as a majority of sales were from first-time buyers.

